66th Southern California Journalism Awards

A big thank you to all who joined us in celebrating the best reporting Southern California has to offer. Click here to check out the winners of the 66th SoCal Journalism Awards and make sure to check out their work!

Stay tuned for photos and videos from the awards gala.

Got a question? Email info@lapressclub.org.

66th SoCal Journalism Awards Red Carpet with Jack Maxwell

Amanda Salas - President’s Award for Impact on Media

Mickey Osterreicher - Guardian Award for Contributions to Press Freedom

Stephen A. Smith - Joseph M. Quinn Award for Lifetime Achievement

Jane Seymour - Bill Rosendahl Public Service Award for Contributions to Civic Life

Evan Gershkovich - Daniel Pearl Award for Courage and Integrity in Journalism

‘Killers of the Flower Moon’ Wins Veritas Award

The Los Angeles Press Club is thrilled to announce Killers of the Flower Moon, produced by Apple Studios and distributed by Paramount Pictures, is the winner of its 9th annual Veritas Award for Best Film Based on or Inspired by Real Events and People.

“This movie, based on in-depth reporting by a dedicated journalist, brought a forgotten piece of American history to a wide audience around the world,” said LA Press Club President Lisa Richwine.

Click here to learn more.

16th National A&E Journalism Awards

Join us in congratulating the winners of the 16th National Arts & Entertainment Journalism Awards! We're truly honored to celebrate the outstanding reporting in this field.

Check out the winners! And click here to see photos from the awards gala.

Barbara Eden - Legend Award for Lifetime Achievement and Contributions to Society

LeVar Burton - Distinguished Storyteller Award for Excellence in Storytelling Outside of Journalism

Henry Louis Gates Jr. - Luminary Award for Career Achievement

Roger Corman - Distinguished Storyteller Award for Excellence in Storytelling Outside of Journalism

65th Southern California Journalism Awards

A big thank you to everyone who joined us to celebrate the best and brightest of Southern California journalism. Check out this year's winners and stay tuned for videos and photos from the evening!

65th Southern Califfornia Journalism Awards - Complete Awards Show

Bernard-Henri Lévy - Daniel Pearl Award for Courage and Integrity in Journalism

Giselle Fernandez - President’s Award for Impact on Media

David Ono - Joseph M. Quinn Award for Lifetime Achievement

65th SoCal Journalism Awards Student Categories Presented by George Pennacchio and Cher Calvin

Gary Sinise - Bill Rosendahl Public Service Award for Contributions to Civic Life

John Leguizamo - President’s Award for Impact on Media

Alene Tchekmedyian - Guardian Award for Contributions to Press Freedom

Press Club Online

Join the LA Press Club for access to our exclusive members-only online programming.

Life in the Time of the Coronavirus Contest

We are thrilled to announce the winners of our Life in the Time of the Coronavirus Contest!

These are challenging times and our entrants bravely and acutely documented their experience living through the COVID-19 pandemic.

First Place winners will receive $1,000. Second Place winners get $500 and Third Place winners get $200 each. All runner-ups will get $100 each. Cash prizes are partly funded by a generous grant from the Hollywood Foreign Press Association.

Click here to see if you're one of the lucky winners! We've published all their amazing work to serve as a historical document of the times. Make sure you check them out!
